#N canvas 24 5 750 350 10;
#X text 5 16 Wilson 11-limit 31-tone scale XH 3, 1975                                        ;
#X text 7   225 Exported from Scala;
#X text 201 225 G. Schiemer 2005;
#X text 7   305 Scala is a tuning analysis-editor-librarian tool; 
#X text 7   315 written by Manuel Op de Coul. It is available as;
#X text 7   325 freeware :- http://www.xs4all.nl/~huygensf/scala;
#N canvas 0 0 400 550 Help 0;
#X text 10 10  Microtonal player written by G. Schiemer 2005;
#X text 10 40  This player allows users to experiment with microtonal tunings in Pure Data;
#X text 10 70  Tunings are generated in Scala and exported to Pure Data;
#X text 10 100 In this player;
#X text 20 120 1. Colour-coded keyboards labelled 'keyboard' are;
#X text 30 135 played manually or driven from a sequencer;
#X text 30 150 - range of each keyboard voice is selected manually;
#X text 40 165 using 'mode' and 'octave';
#X text 20 190 2. Melodic contour is modified using binary switches;
#X text 30 205 - clear all switches to play ascending scale; 
#X text 30 220 - set all switches to play descending scales; 
#X text 20 245 3. Each voice is manually enabled or disabled using;
#X text 30 260 its corresponding 'mute' button;
#X text 30 275 - any 1 of 8 combinations of 3 voices is selected;
#X text 40 290 by a single button operation using 'voices';
#X text 30 305 - sequencer clock is started or stopped;
#X text 40 320 using 'master' button;
#X text 20 345 4. Each voice has a clock that is manually enabled;
#X text 30 360 or disabled using its corresponding button;
#X text 30 375 - any 1 of 8 combinations of 3 'clocks' can be;
#X text 40 390 sequenced by a single button operation;
#X text 20 415 5. Specification of each scale step is displayed;
#X text 30 430 by opening .scl on the main canvas;
#X text 30 445 - new scales can be played by running the;
#X text 20 470 6. Scala command file with a new scale selected;
#X text 30 485 - keyboard size is automatically determined by scale chosen;
#X text 10 510 Changes to this file may be made either in PD or by modifying Scala scripts - Greg S;
#X restore 255 265 pd Help ;
